}}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== A "Declaration for models" document submitted to the FCC suggests that :[[ZyXEL WAC6303D-S|WAC6303D-S]] and [[ZyXEL NWA1123-AC SHD|NWA1123-AC SHD]] are electrically identical. * [[ZyXEL WAC6303D-S]]: 802.11ac Wave 2 Dual-Radio Unified Pro Access Point * [[ZyXEL NWA1123-AC SHD|NWA1123-AC SHD]]: 802.11ac Wave 2 Dual-Radio Managed Access Point <!--{{FCC ST|05/17/2018|indexme.}}--> This [[ZyXEL NWA1123-AC SHD]] may be marketed under different names like :[[ZyXEL NWA1123-AC v2|NWA1123-AC v2]] or [[ZyXEL NWA1123-AC PRO|NWA1123-AC PRO]] mentioned on [[ZyXEL NWA1123-AC|NWA1123-AC]]. <small> :A "Product Equality Declaration" document declares that the differences between these two :devices under FCC ID I88WAC6303D-S and devices covered under the I88NWA5123-ACHD :entry are the latter lacks Bluetooth and they use different Wi-Fi antennas. </small>
